Sentencas: This article presents the successful testing of 70% w/w samarium-doped ceria mixed with 30% w/w barium carbonate (SDC/BC) electrolyte for use as an improved electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization and Performance of a Samarium-Doped Ceria/Barium Carbonate Composite Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The phase changes, particle size distribution, morphology, electrochemical impedance, conductivity, and maximum power density of the fuel cell based on this SDC/BC composite electrolyte are discussed.
Titulo: Characterization and Performance of a Samarium-Doped Ceria/Barium Carbonate Composite Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The SDC/BC electrolyte is chemically compatible with a Ni-SDC/BC anode.
Titulo: Characterization and Performance of a Samarium-Doped Ceria/Barium Carbonate Composite Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of the SDC/BC is 102.7 mS cm(-1) at 600 degrees C with an activation energy of 36.12 kJ mol(-1).
Titulo: Characterization and Performance of a Samarium-Doped Ceria/Barium Carbonate Composite Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The maximum power output of the Ni-SDC-BC/SDC-BC/Pt cell is 427 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C, which is attributed to the high electrochemical activity of both the electrolyte and the anode material.
Titulo: Characterization and Performance of a Samarium-Doped Ceria/Barium Carbonate Composite Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that SDC/BC has potential as a low-temperature electrolyte for LT-SOFC.
Titulo: Characterization and Performance of a Samarium-Doped Ceria/Barium Carbonate Composite Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
